Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.64,0:00:13.40,Magus-Episode_Title,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1500,1500)}Those Awaiting a Star\N {\fs20}Part 3
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.99,0:00:21.70,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to deliver that\Nbook to someone for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.20,0:00:24.79,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.38,0:00:30.42,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:35.55,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Stay here, and you'll really \Nbe unable to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.52,0:00:44.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.64,0:00:46.52,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,This is my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:50.86,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,It's the regret that's been \Nwoven shut inside that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.36,0:00:56.53,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,That night, I had a promise \NI needed to fulfill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:00:57.99,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.28,0:01:01.08,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.87,0:01:03.50,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Niikura Mayumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:05.87,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,The owner of that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.59,0:01:11.84,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Which one are you going to borrow today?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:13.51,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I can't decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:16.59,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,The master's books are all so impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.55,0:01:21.60,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,When they say "bookworm," they \Nmust mean people like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.97,0:01:24.56,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Not as much as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.73,0:01:30.06,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.06,0:01:32.02,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,The master told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.40,0:01:34.94,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,that you were going to get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.03,0:01:38.45,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.07,0:01:43.12,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you're going to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.49,0:01:47.08,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,What more could I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.08,0:01:54.00,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,My happiest moments are when\N I'm reading the last page of a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.51,0:01:57.51,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,The story ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.26,0:02:07.31,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,But it makes me feel as though \Nit's going to go on somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:10.15,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,You can borrow this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:15.15,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.49,0:02:20.11,Magus-flashback,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't forget to give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.57,0:02:24.37,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I was just a lowly student.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.08,0:02:28.33,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,She was the daughter of \Nthe wealthy family I was indebted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.21,0:02:33.84,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought our relationship \Nwould ever bear fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:36.88,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.34,0:02:41.09,sign_10553_88_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me on the final platform
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.32,0:03:01.03,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,She extended her hand to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:06.16,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice but to go to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:08.95,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:39.49,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:48.79,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.24,0:03:50.50,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.25,0:03:52.50,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:06.68,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I was drawn to this library.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.11,0:05:12.79,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And I became a captive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.97,0:05:33.47,Magus-internal/narrator,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know how \Nlong I've been here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:37.52,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.36,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You reminded me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.44,0:05:48.15,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,When you smiled and said you \Nlike the last page of a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:52.37,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,To her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.04,0:05:54.66,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,To Niikura Mayumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.96,0:05:58.04,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:07.22,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one else I can ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.05,0:06:09.39,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:12.64,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:28.15,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.95,0:06:40.54,Default,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,No one will ever wander into here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:34.93,sign_17622_111_Niikura,,0000,0000,0000,,Niikura
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:50.36,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:51.95,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Niikura Mayumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.78,0:07:55.99,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.28,0:07:57.66,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,My great-grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.79,0:08:00.50,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,You're from this neighborhood, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:04.12,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma Mayumi's in the hospital right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.42,0:08:07.84,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,You know the huge hospital by the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:09.30,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,She's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:11.09,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,What did you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:13.51,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,We just got here yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:14.97,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,We don't really know our way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:16.72,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,If you need something...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.72,0:08:18.01,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:26.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Niikura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:29.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,With all due respect, \Nhow are you two related?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:35.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I can't tell you her \Nroom number unless you're related.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:38.74,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Niikura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:43.83,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I think her grandchildren's families \Nwere coming to visit today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:45.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.46,0:08:46.83,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:48.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:57.55,sign_21200_145_Spring_Will_Be_M - Copy,,0000,0000,0000,,Niikura Mayumi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.55,0:08:58.89,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Niikura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.89,0:09:00.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're out of bed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.76,0:09:02.68,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:05.85,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,I've read all the books I brought with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.27,0:09:08.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Your great-granddaughter's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:10.15,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.15,0:09:11.94,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,She's here early.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.58,0:09:24.37,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you going to eat lunch first?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:30.04,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.47,0:09:45.68,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:53.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Niikura Mayumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.94,0:09:55.15,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.41,0:10:05.16,sign_21200_145_Spring_Will_Be_M,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Spring Will Be Missed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.17,0:10:15.92,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,This book... Where did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.99,0:10:39.70,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.86,0:10:42.37,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,This is my book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:45.87,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,This is {\i1}our{\i0} book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.25,0:10:50.00,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you his granddaughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:52.50,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,His {\i1}great{\i0}-granddaughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.63,0:10:57.80,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Is he doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.88,0:11:02.05,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:03.93,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.81,0:11:06.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.85,0:11:10.77,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.73,0:11:13.77,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:19.90,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,He never did come to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:25.03,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,but he did fulfill his promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:30.25,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,He gave this book back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.00,0:11:33.46,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.79,0:11:37.34,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.67,0:11:44.22,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Let me get a good look at your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.18,0:11:47.06,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:53.56,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:11:57.27,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.32,0:12:07.87,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.50,0:12:22.84,Default,Mayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Hatori Chise-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:50.20,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma, shouldn't you be asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.12,0:12:50.04,Magus-overlap,Micromayumi female,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmama, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.04,0:12:51.62,Magus-overlap,Micromayumi female,0000,0000,0000,,I got second rank in swimming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.08,0:12:54.58,Default,Micromayumi male,0000,0000,0000,,I got third rank!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:57.29,Default,Micromayumi female,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and get better, Grandmama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.92,0:12:58.63,Magus-overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.29,0:12:58.96,Default,Micromayumi male,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:01.17,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Did a girl come by?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.46,0:13:04.17,Default,Minimayumi,0000,0000,0000,,Red hair, about this tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.39,0:13:14.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:15.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:17.15,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.15,0:13:19.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are we really going \Nto the forest today?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.94,0:13:21.86,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Are you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:24.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault if we get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.57,0:13:25.90,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,We won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:52.89,sign_26666_186_The_Lonely_Littl,Text,0000,0000,0000,,The Lonely Little Star
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:03.44,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I gave her the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.74,0:14:08.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mayumi-san said, "Thank you."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:14.29,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,"The child of a star asked,\Nwith a voice like a bell,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:21.25,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,'God of the Stars, why do you leave\Nme here by myself in this dark night sky?'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:28.80,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,'I have no way to talk to the other stars, \Nor to show each other our light.'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.59,0:14:33.68,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,To which the God of the Stars replied,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.26,0:14:36.89,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,'Look {\i1}very{\i0} carefully.'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.56,0:14:44.36,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And so the child looked very hard. So hard \Nthat their eyes could have fallen out."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:53.95,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Then, off in the distance, a myriad\Nof tiny, twinkling stars could be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.83,0:14:58.12,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,'See? You can see them if \Nyou look really carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.62,0:15:01.25,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,The sky is endlessly connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.79,0:15:06.63,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Just try, and you'll see even \Nthe faintest of lights.'"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.80,0:15:13.30,Magus-flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This is the book I need?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:15.14,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Hatori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:15.93,Magus-flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.18,0:15:21.77,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You might see nothing but\Npitch-black darkness right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.56,0:15:28.74,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,But, you have to keep trying and \Ntrying, looking into the dark world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.65,0:15:31.41,Magus-flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:36.99,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And off in the distance, \Nyou'll surely find some light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:40.46,Magus-flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Like the child of a star?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:41.29,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:42.62,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Like the child of a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:51.09,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And when you find the child of \Na star, they'll surely find you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.22,0:15:55.14,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll shine light on each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.06,0:15:59.93,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,And then your world will \Nno longer be pitch-black.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.64,0:16:01.98,Magus-flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.60,0:16:03.65,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.48,0:16:08.90,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many stars out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.99,0:16:17.41,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I truly believe you'll meet a child \Nof a star who will light your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.45,0:16:19.70,Magus-flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.33,0:16:25.71,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Life is a lot longer than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.42,0:16:29.71,Magus-flashback,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,Live your best, and you will...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:47.31,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.86,0:16:53.86,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.86,0:16:56.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We're ready when you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.75,0:17:12.92,Magus-flashbackinternal,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,I truly believe you'll meet a child \Nof a star who will light your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:11.92,Magus-top,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Boys, can you come help?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:12.92,sign_31475_221_The_Lonely_Littl,,0000,0000,0000,,The Lonely Little Star
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.92,0:17:12.92,Magus-top,A,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.68,0:17:15.63,Magus-flashbackinternal,Miura,0000,0000,0000,,You will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:22.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this book \Nis here, after I let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.64,0:17:23.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Show me more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:25.60,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.19,0:17:29.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:31.11,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, may I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.37,0:17:42.08,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.12,0:17:44.20,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.17,0:17:50.88,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That story you just told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:54.05,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I've seen \Nsomething like it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.01,0:17:57.93,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:01.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,"Mayoiga"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.35,0:18:03.10,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:09.65,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It shows itself in a spectacular light \Nto those who get lost in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.27,0:18:13.23,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it draws people in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.82,0:18:15.07,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.07,0:18:16.49,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That's so odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:17.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:24.79,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Those who wander in are allowed \Nto bring home just one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:30.50,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You don't see this kind of \Nthing very often around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:33.92,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,People do steal things by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:36.51,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:41.05,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably the condition for \Ntheir returning to their own world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.76,0:18:50.10,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That Miura man gave you something every \Ntime you left from the library, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:55.40,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A library card, a picture \Nbook, and that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.69,0:19:00.20,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it counts if it's \Ngiven to you by someone inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:03.16,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What if you can't be given anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:06.95,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You'd likely be stuck there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:12.21,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it means to \Nwander into the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:19.96,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Though I don't know how \Nmuch he was aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.10,0:19:23.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miura-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.75,0:19:27.08,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He must have known everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.36,0:19:30.42,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He must have given the \Nbook to me knowing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.33,0:19:32.54,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.86,0:19:39.55,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,If it wasn't {\i1}that{\i0} book that he'd given me, \NI probably wouldn't have left him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.47,0:19:42.39,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.39,0:19:43.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.48,0:19:45.52,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Is this memory a painful one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.16,0:19:51.49,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Angie really shouldn't have sent us this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:54.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.03,0:19:55.16,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.58,0:19:59.21,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind this book, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.40,0:20:00.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.57,0:20:01.65,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.24,0:20:11.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's already getting dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.77,0:20:14.28,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,We've really been talking away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.17,0:20:32.21,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't finish cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:34.86,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,We can continue tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.86,0:20:35.62,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.98,0:20:38.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's way past tea time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.25,0:20:40.50,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Stare...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.50,0:20:41.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Silky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.69,0:20:44.17,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You made tea for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.04,0:20:48.34,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.34,0:20:50.51,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have it with dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.96,0:20:58.20,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you want to make \Na promise like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.20,0:21:00.13,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll... I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.81,0:21:03.83,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,All right, it's time for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:07.79,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be chicken stewed with tomatoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.87,0:21:13.42,Default,Dog,0000,0000,0000,,tomato compote, and dried tomato muffins.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.40,0:21:19.26,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,There sure are plenty of \Ntomatoes during the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.65,0:21:31.71,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, what are you going to \Ndo with that picture book?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.28,0:21:36.68,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll give it another \Nproper read through.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.63,0:21:42.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I can read it \Ndifferently this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.97,0:21:49.31,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, would you talk \Nto me about it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.63,0:21:53.31,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.64,0:23:32.64,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,There's more to the "Mayoiga" story.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.64,0:23:34.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,There's more?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.93,0:23:41.08,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who takes something home from \Nthat house is met with good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.86,0:23:46.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,That might be true.
